Arabidopsis.AGI: Although HP55 appears to be only conserved in the Eurosids II lineage, ribosome profiling suggests that it is functional (ref. 10).
Homology group (HG): classification based on sequence conservation between diverse angioperms
mORF: gene name (where known) or AGI of main ORF associated with a particular CPuORF
rCUTS: signals/molecules that induce repressive CUTS
aCUTS: signals/molecules that induce activating CUTS
CPuORF class: based on patterns of sequence conservation (see ref. 92)

uAUG start?: most CPuORFs are translated from a canonical upstream start codon (uAUG), however there is recent evidence to suggest that several CPuORFs may be translated from a non-canonical start codon (Y=uAUG; N=non-canonical start)

Identification methodology: CPuORFs have been identified using a variety of different approaches. Here we indicate (in green) which CPuORF was identified in which studies (see appropriate reference shown at the top of each column)

intercistronic distance (nt): length of sequence between the CPuORF coding region and the mORF. For those transcripts with multiple CPuORFs, only the distance between the most 3'-CPuORF and the mORF is shown
Notes: known or predicted functions of each mORF
Identification method: Methodology used to identify each CPuORF. Many CPuORFs have been identified using multiple approaches, but only the first instance is shown here.
Highlighted in red are the main CPuORFs examined in this study
